.TH "unmap_mapping_pages" 9 "unmap_mapping_pages" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
unmap_mapping_pages \- Unmap pages from processes.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" unmap_mapping_pages
.BI "(struct address_space *mapping "  ","
.BI "pgoff_t start "  ","
.BI "pgoff_t nr "  ","
.BI "bool even_cows "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mapping" 12
The address space containing pages to be unmapped.
.IP "start" 12
Index of first page to be unmapped.
.IP "nr" 12
Number of pages to be unmapped.  0 to unmap to end of file.
.IP "even_cows" 12
Whether to unmap even private COWed pages.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Unmap the pages in this address space from any userspace process which
has them mmaped.  Generally, you want to remove COWed pages as well when
a file is being truncated, but not when invalidating pages from the page
cache.
